threadlocal-kotlin
==================

A Kotlin Multiplatform port of the Rust `thread_local` crate.

The upstream Rust source is dual-licensed Apache-2.0 OR MIT, copyright
Amanieu d'Antras (https://github.com/Amanieu/thread_local-rs). The
Kotlin translation here is a derivative work, distributed under the
same dual Apache-2.0 OR MIT terms. All algorithmic and structural
design credit — the bucket-of-power-of-two layout, the
`BinaryHeap<Reverse<usize>>` thread-ID recycler, the lock-free
`Entry` / `ThreadLocal` invariants, the `RawIter` state machine —
belongs to the upstream author.

Each ported `.kt` file under
`src/commonMain/kotlin/io/github/kotlinmania/threadlocal/` carries a
one-line attribution comment naming the upstream `.rs` file it was
translated from.

